    "body": "1) Players tab would be the same - everything there seems to be logical. The only thing I would change - \"Slot Admin\" button. I would place it on top so you won't need to scroll down all the way down to reach it. Or you can make buttons always on top (out of players scroll list).\nOr functions can be separated on different buttons. Like this:\n![orateams](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/17611709/13493198/bb048b12-e14d-11e5-93f9-84d373c41334.jpg)\nDifferent setup functions can be placed on top of list: configure teams, configure bots, configure colors for players (I miss the standart 8 color pallette, though).\n\n2) Music control - well, I don't know the real reason why player control can't be placed in the corner of the screen as small simple panel. \"Prev, Play / Pause, Next, Shuffle On/Off, Select track (popup list)\". Then you can change music anywhere from main menu to depth of mission selection or map selection.\n![oraplay](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/17611709/13493504/839c5978-e14f-11e5-9501-ce380e212f9a.jpg)\n"
  },
