    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "With regards to the player tab, I mean the specific design implementation: in our existing UIs tabs are attached to the top or bottom of a scrollpanel or bin.  The player bin has a static row of labels (which don't scroll) above the scrollpanel, and the player rows are then inside the bin (which do scroll).  Placing the tabs at the top means either removing the labels, moving them inside the bin, or having a scroll panel nested inside a bin: none of these are very good options.  This is why we placed the tabs at the bottom.\n"
  },
